name: Subway
directions: In the subway in the back to the right
comment: They are extremely nice people you dont have to worry about not being allowed to use the restroom

name: Taco Bell
directions: Turn right into the hallway as soon as you enter. There should be a two, gendered bathrooms that are single bathrooms.
comment: Google says the entrance is wheelchair accessible, so I marked it as accessible. I hope this is correct. There also may be a changing table, but I didn't want to incorrectly mark it.

name: Casey's (Gas Station)
directions: Walk to the left through the aisles and into the little hallway. There should be two, gendered bathrooms but they are single bathrooms.
comment: There may be a changing room, I can't recall for certain and I didn't want to incorrectly mark it as being available if it is not.

name: Cottonwood Station Eatery
directions: Two gender-neutral restrooms located on the left side of the patio at the top of the stairs.

name: The Equality center
directions: The center has several accessible and non accessible restrooms throughout the building.
comment: I’m pretty sure they will let you use the bathroom even if that’s all you’re there for. They also have free condoms and dental dams available.

name: Quills coffee
directions: In the back up a ramp

name: The Tipping Point
comment: Customers only.

name: Shades of Brown Coffee and Art
directions: Two single “stall” unisex bathrooms in the building. One beyond the bar and dishroom to the right, the other slightly further through a door frame and to the left. Typically, they will let you use the bathroom without buying, they may be more strict if it is very busy or if you do this often.
comment: The light switch for the second bathroom is outside of the door, a tricky find.

name: Rudenstams Gårdsbutik & Kafé
directions: Go in through the entrance, turn right and continue down the aisle until you reach the fruit and vegetables section to the right. Then go around the wall at the end of the aisle and there you’ll find the bathrooms.
comment: While you’re there I really recommend their food, it’s delicious.

name: M
directions: The equality center has several accessible and non accessible all gender bathrooms
comment: I’m pretty sure they’ll let you use them even if your only there to use the bathroom. They also have free condoms/dental dams available.

name: Sook Pastry
comment: You have to be a paying customer

name: Salon Benders
directions: Through Trans friendly salon. Say Hi to Jessie and Cal. In back on right
comment: Trans owned and queer friendly

name: The Waterfront shops toilet
directions: Outside entrance attached to Barr-ee shop.

name: Eric Anderson
directions: At the back of the store
comment: Paying customers only

name: Café Herzstück
directions: It's a single stall hidden inside
comment: You have to be a customer

name: Starbucks
comment: as of July 2020 closed due to covid19

name: Bathrooms at Ayer Public Library
directions: 1st Floor, accessible by stairs and elevator. 2 restrooms, accessible to anyone
comment: Ask staff at front desk if you have trouble finding the bathrooms- all staff is very kind and helpful

name: Starbucks Chelsea and Westminster hospital
directions: To the left as you walk in.

name: The Pumpernickel Inn & Cafe
directions: Through the seated area of the cafe, up the ramp through the double doors, on the right, next to the kitchen.
comment: For paying customers only (but sometimes the waitress will turn a blind eye) There are two bathrooms next to each other, they are technically gendered, but not really, you may use whichever one you’d like to use. Only the first one is accessible, the second one is narrow

name: The Pumpernickel Inn & Cafe
directions: On the side with Gelato, behind the coffee counter, in the back corner next to the drink coolers
comment: Open to paying customers only (but sometimes the person working turns a blind eye)

name: Sunshine Laundromat
directions: Back right corner

name: Dulles Town Center
directions: There’s at least one gender neutral (family) bathroom in the mall, on the first floor. It’s right below Old Navy and Forever 21.
comment: It has a low sink, a high sink, a changing table, toilet, and a urinal next to the toilet

name: Walmart
directions: Back of the store by the baby section.
comment: Door to the left as you walk to the gendered bathrooms, family washroom.

name: JS Chinese Restaurant
directions: In back of restaurant, past the sign that says "bathrooms" and to the left.
comment: Requires walking up a couple steps so it's not wheelchair accessible

name: 6th floor lobby restroom in the 2525 building
directions: 6th floor in the lobby to the north of the elevators
comment: This building is for Vanderbilt students and employees of a couple businesses—it is publicly accessible. As long as it’s within normal business hours, this bathroom is accessible to the general community. There are two main entrances; escalators are available to the second floor elevators by the Starbucks, and elevators from the first floor are available from the west building entrance.

name: 16-Bit Bar and Arcade
directions: Go back to the right of the bar. Restrooms are behind where the vending machine usually is. Outside of bathrooms area is a chalk wall.
comment: Unless it is a "bring your kids" day and you have someone 21+ there; only people of legal drinking age allowed. They usually card at the door.

name: Dirty Frank's Hot Dog Palace
directions: In the back hallway past the bar and kitchen window. Right side.

name: Gisela Vega
street: University of Miami, University Whitten Center, 1306 Stanford Drive, Suite  2300K, 2nd Floor
directions: 2nd Floor Whitten University Center
comment: This needs to be updated to add gender inclusive and  Changing table please.  Thank you.

name: Vancouver Public Library - Marpole Branch
directions: In children's section to the right of returns/service desk

name: Granville Safeway
directions: Near front of store across from escalators

name: Citizen Burger Bar
directions: Straight back on the right. Two restroom doors that lock from the inside if in use. They are private gender neutral stalls.
comment: You can walk in and use the restroom without being a customer

name: Joann's Fabrics and Crafts
directions: To the back near the yarn
comment: Includes 1 family/unisex bathroom as well as gendered 1 stall bathrooms.

name: Kafe Leopold
comment: A row of non-gendered single stalls with full doors

name: The Flying Duck
directions: Go down the stairs and through the door to the main bar. Across from the bar (next to the stage) you will see two doors marked urinals/stalls
comment: One room is urinals, one is just stalls

name: Brewchachos' Restrooms
directions: In the front to the right, both doors have a figure with a skeletal face painted on them. You'll see women's first and men's is on the other side of the women's.
comment: You have to be a paying customer or plan to buy something after using the restroom.

name: Georgetown Cupcake
directions: Straight in the back, to the right of the kitchen
comment: Anyone can use the bathroom, not just customers. Bathroom is up a few stairs, ask an employee for help if you need to use the wheelchair ramp!

name: Chatham University: Science Complex: Laboratory Building and Buhl Hall
directions: "All gender" single occupancy restroom. On floor one (not basement/floor zero) opposite the women's bathroom. Converted previous men's room with urinal and single large stall including hand bars. Main door and stall both lock. Enter through west side door and turn right for shortest route door-to-bathroom.
comment: The bathroom is available for people in the Chatham community, such as students, faculty & staff and their families, people touring the campus, and event attendees.

name: 10020 Joplin St, Commerce City, CO 80022, USA
comment: There’s two gendered restrooms, doesn’t truly matter which one you use. Both are 100% safe to use until they’re locked at night.

name: 15051 E 104th Ave, Commerce City, CO 80022, USA
comment: Free to use. They have two restrooms, two gendered with stalls (safe) and two non gendered unisex. Gendered restrooms are by the Starbucks. Non gendered restrooms are back by the pharmacy

name: HEB
directions: Front of the store
comment: Family Restroom

name: Coulter Cafe
directions: Two gender neutral bathrooms at the rear of the cafe.
comment: For paying customers.

name: Rhythm city casino resort
directions: All the way to back in main hall

name: Northside Marketplace
directions: In the front door to the right.
comment: 2 gender neutral bathrooms.  Very clean!

name: Huckleberries
directions: back of store

name: Panhandle animal shelter
directions: In the cat area by the entrance to the thrift store

name: Goodwill
directions: On the right as you enter
comment: Gender neutral, single stall restrooms.

name: Star and Shadow Cinema
directions: Accessible toilet to the right of the building behind the box office . Gender neutral cubicles are through the orange and straight ahead .
comment: During a club night you would need a ticket to enter , when the cafe is open use of the toilets is open also!

name: Alley Cat Cafe
directions: Go through the plexiglass door in the back right corner of the cafe,  next to the cat room, the second door on your left is the bathroom
comment: Owned and run by queer folx, welcome home. Don’t need to be a customer, ‘cause you’re family. ❤️

name: 1004 Cosby Hwy, Newport, TN 37821, USA
comment: Door lock was broke though

name: Apparel City
comment: Be a paying customer

name: Baño público
directions: En paseo de don José Anselmo Clavé

name: Murphy's USA Private Restroom
directions: Located on east side of the building. Indoor lock, air-conditioned and ventilated (though not WELL ventilated). Sometimes busy when buses come in.

name: South Belt Walmart Family Bathroom
directions: In the back of the store, located near electronics. Single room, one toilet, changing station, hanging hook for purses or change of clothing and periodically cleaned/stocked.

name: HEB
directions: Family Restroom

name: 990 W 59th Ave, Vancouver, BC V6P 1X9, Canada
directions: By side entrance/down hallway to left of main lobby. 2nd one upstairs directly above main lobby.

name: Samuel
directions: Tropical smoothie cafe, In the back on the right
comment: We don't really pay attention to who goes in and out of what bathroom plus we don't really care, I'm a trans male who works there

name: Almost home
directions: It’s a restaurant in Salem, or
comment: It’s a handicap restroom but it’s unisex single stall

name: Almost home
directions: It’s a single bathroom it says handicap but they never say anything to me

name: Breadboard Bakery
comment: One bathroom has a table that could probs be used as a changing table.  Both bathrooms are large, unisex single-stalls.  Probably fine to use them not as a customer, but the baked goods are delicious, so treat yourself if you can afford to.

name: Mosgo’s Coffee House
directions: In the back of the store near the self serve water station.
comment: You or your party have to be a paying customer to get the keys behind the counter/register. It is possible to grab the keys after the other person comes out but you have to remember to return them behind the counter/register.

name: New World Water
directions: Imagine the layout of the store as a horse shoe, it is in the back near the small and large water bottles being sold.
comment: The female store owner is really nice but also it doesn’t hurt to act like you are browsing for a bit then ask. Once in awhile you will encounter a male there, partner of the female. They do have small items if you are genuinely interested in buying. They have locally made products like chocolates, stickers, candles, crystals, lip balms and more.

name: Target
comment: Family bathroom

name: Music & Arts
directions: Back of store and to the left

name: Kessler Park United Methodist Church
directions: Church is on corner of Colorado/Turner, multiple baths inside.
comment: LBGTQIA-welcoming congregation,  use whichever bathrooms you wish!

name: Target
directions: Main floor, past hall to gendered bathrooms, by customer service desk.

name: Meridian highschool
directions: Through front doors 1st hall on your right near the end there's a genderless bathroom. Through front doors 1st hall on your left there's 2 gendered bathrooms. More in the 2nd hall on your left as well.
comment: You have to be a student, parent of a student, or staff member to use them

name: 5 Below
directions: To the back left
comment: 2 family restrooms, one with changing table

name: 5 Below
directions: All the way to the back left, 2 family bathrooms

name: Brewdog
directions: Up the stairs, in the back corner.

name: Cambridge University Students Union
directions: Upstairs, at the back of the lounge through two double doors. Or downstairs, in the corridor.
comment: Access is via two sets of stairs or an accessible lift.

name: Inova Loudoun Hospital
directions: North entrance.   Main lobby.  Top of the stairs on the left.  Also throughout the building.

name: Inova Loudoun Hospial
comment: North entrance.  Main lobby,  up the stairs on the left.

name: Los Alamos Co-op Market
directions: As you come in the doors immediately turn left and then turn left again when you see a seating area. Continue to the back of the seating area, there should be a hall on your right with two single stall “family” restrooms.

name: Denny’s
comment: Walked I. As though I was waiting for the rest of my party and just going to use bathroom while waiting.

name: The Sideboard at Cape Fear Games
directions: Back of the cafe past the ordering counter
comment: The hallway is a little bit narrow to get back to the bathroom and there are games you have to walk past. You have to be a paying customer.

name: Baño público
directions: Según entras al parque por la plaza de las Cigarreras

name: Garraxi
directions: Piso de arriba
comment: Es un restaurante

name: At Home
directions: On the front wall of the store to the right of the entrance with the gendered bathrooms

name: Restaurant Chez Charles
directions:
Dans la première partie à droite il a des toilettes genrées à une personne et dans la deuxième partie à gauche il y a des toilettes non genrées

In the first part to the right there are gendered one person bathrooms and in the second part to the left there's a gender neutral bathroom
comment: Vous devriez probablement mangé là/You should probably eat there

name: Crosby’s Marketplace
directions: Go all the way to the back of the store. To the right of the milk shelves there is a pair of big double doors. Do NOT go through these doors, but on the right side of the doorway is the single bathroom.

name: The Unitarian Universalist Society
directions: When you come in through the front door, go up the stairs to the big room. At the back of the room (just before you reach the stage) on the left, there is a doorway leading down stairs to another floor (this floor is visible from the doorway and the stairs are shallow). When you reach this floor, turn right and soon the bathroom will be on the right!
